@startuml SD_17_Notification
' ============================================================
' SEQUENCE DIAGRAM - Notification System
' FR-40: Create + Display + Mark Read Notifications
' ============================================================

title **SD-17: Notification System\n(Create → Display → Mark as Read)**

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam sequence {
    ParticipantBackgroundColor #E0F7FA
    ParticipantBorderColor #00838F
    ArrowColor #00838F
}

actor "User\n(All Roles)" as User #LightBlue
participant "Browser" as Browser #LightYellow
participant "NotificationServlet\n(API)" as Controller #E0F7FA
participant "NotificationService" as Service #E8F5E9
participant "NotificationDAO" as DAO #FFF3E0
database "SQL Server" as DB #F3E5F5

== Part A: Notification is Created (by System) ==

note over Service
  Notifications are created by various system events:
  - Order confirmed → Customer
  - Event approved/rejected → Organizer
  - New support ticket → Assignee
  - New chat message → Recipient
  - Account banned → User
end note

Service -> DAO: create(notification)
activate DAO
DAO -> DB: INSERT INTO Notifications (\n  notificationId, userId,\n  type, message,\n  relatedEventId (nullable),\n  relatedOrderId (nullable),\n  isRead=0, createdAt\n)
activate DB
DB --> DAO: Created
deactivate DB
DAO --> Service: OK
deactivate DAO

== Part B: User Views Notifications ==

User -> Browser: Click bell icon 🔔
Browser -> Controller: GET /api/notifications\n?unreadOnly=true
activate Controller
Controller -> Service: getNotifications(\nuserId, unreadOnly)
activate Service
Service -> DAO: findByUser(userId, unreadOnly)
activate DAO
DAO -> DB: SELECT * FROM Notifications\nWHERE userId = ?\nAND (isRead = 0 OR ? = false)\nORDER BY createdAt DESC\nOFFSET 0 ROWS FETCH NEXT 20 ROWS ONLY
activate DB
DB --> DAO: List<Notification>
deactivate DB
DAO --> Service: notifications
deactivate DAO
Service --> Controller: notifications
deactivate Service
Controller --> Browser: JSON {notifications: [...],\nunreadCount: 5}
deactivate Controller
Browser --> User: 🔔 Notification dropdown:\n• Event "Summer Music"\n  has been approved ✨\n• Order ORD-A1B2C3\n  payment confirmed ✅\n• New message from\n  organizer 💬\n+ 2 more...

== Part C: Mark as Read ==

User -> Browser: Click on a notification
Browser -> Controller: POST /api/notifications/read\n{notificationId}
activate Controller
Controller -> Service: markAsRead(\nnotificationId, userId)
activate Service
Service -> DAO: markRead(notificationId)
activate DAO
DAO -> DB: UPDATE Notifications SET\nisRead = 1\nWHERE notificationId = ?\nAND userId = ?
activate DB
DB --> DAO: Updated
deactivate DB
DAO --> Service: OK
deactivate DAO
Service --> Controller: OK
deactivate Service
Controller --> Browser: JSON {success: true}
deactivate Controller
Browser -> Browser: Update UI:\n- Remove unread indicator\n- Decrease unread count

== Part D: Mark All as Read ==

User -> Browser: Click "Mark all as read"
Browser -> Controller: POST /api/notifications/read-all
activate Controller
Controller -> Service: markAllAsRead(userId)
activate Service
Service -> DAO: markAllRead(userId)
activate DAO
DAO -> DB: UPDATE Notifications SET\nisRead = 1\nWHERE userId = ?\nAND isRead = 0
activate DB
DB --> DAO: Updated (5 rows)
deactivate DB
DAO --> Service: OK
deactivate DAO
Service --> Controller: OK
deactivate Service
Controller --> Browser: JSON {success: true,\nmarked: 5}
deactivate Controller
Browser --> User: ✅ All notifications\nmarked as read

@enduml
